content.p: Several thousands of students from Malaysia have studied at The University of Nottingham since it gained University status in 1948 and there are currently over 750 students from Malaysia studying at the University. The University has maintained close relations with former students through Persatuan Siswazah Nottingham, and through personal connections, academic exchanges and research links. Many prominent members of Malaysian society are Nottingham graduates, including former Agongs, politicians, ambassadors and leaders of business and industry: Jalan Broga, 43500 Semenyih Selangor Darul Ehsan Malaysia THE UNIVERSITY OF NOTTINGHAM IN MALAYSIA SDN.
